    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look primed for a high-ceiling outing today, headlined by three standout plays. **Luis Robert Jr.** (75.28) leads the charge with an elite matchup against Quintana; despite a slight headwind penalty, his massive platoon advantage against the lefty and a favorable xERA of 5.04 make him our primary offensive anchor. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** (73.16) benefits significantly from the wind blowing out, providing a sturdy floor against Imanaga, while **Jackson Merrill** (67.91) rounds out our top-tier tier by capitalizing on a prime spot in the order against Nelson. While we remain aggressive on stolen base threats like **Josh Lowe** and **Andy Pages**, these three are the engine for our Roto categories today.\n\nStrategic lineup construction forced a difficult decision regarding the bench, specifically with **Gunnar Henderson**. Despite his pedigree, **Gunnar Henderson** (53.01) was ultimately benched due to a matchup against Early, whose 2.34 xERA significantly depresses the projection. In a high-efficiency game cap environment, we prioritize the favorable xERA matchups\u2014like that of **Nolan Schanuel** (61.02) against Lugo\u2014over the raw talent of **Gunnar Henderson** or **Marcell Ozuna** (51.73). We are also monitoring the risk profile of our middle infield: while **Nasim Nunez** (60.54) has been elevated by his stolen base profile, the matchup against Hudson presents a lower scoring floor than our core OF. We are proceeding with this configuration to maximize our efficiency-per-start ratio across the board.",
